script.line: Where are you going? You have a rehearsal about to start.

script.name: Liz
script.line: I stole a baby, Jack. I'm taking a half day.

script.name: Jack
script.line: Fair enough.

script.name: Liz
script.line: I have to do some thinking.

script.name: Liz
script.line: Maybe it's impossible to have it all... the career, the family.

script.name: Liz
script.line: But if anybody can figure out how to do it, it's me.

script.name: Jack
script.line: That's going up.

script.name: Liz
script.line: Aw, nerds!

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: I was talking about you at work today, Mother.

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: I think my boss, Mr. Jack Donaghy, wishes you were his mother.

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: Isn't that something, Mother?

script.name: Kenneth's Mother
script.line: Yes, Kenneth. That's sweet.

script.name: Kenneth's Mother
script.line: Do you have me on speakerphone again?

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: Yes, ma'am. It's just like "Charlie's Angels."

script.name: Kenneth's Mother
script.line: Oh, by the way, did you get your old Halloween decorations I sent you?

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: Oh, yes! Thank you.

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: I'm looking at the kooky skeleton right now. I love it.

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: You're the best mother in the whole world.

script.name: Kenneth's Mother
script.line: Okay. Calm down, dear.

script.name: Kenneth
script.line: Yes, Mother.
